{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Add Automatic Action Item Extraction & Kanban Integration for Crisp\n\nAutomate the extraction of action items from Crisp conversations and surface them immediately on the Meeting Details page, eliminating the need for manual extraction. Extracted items assigned to the user should be automatically added to a configurable Kanban board.\n\n---\n\nSettings: Default Kanban Board Selection\n\n- Add a \"Default Kanban Board\" dropdown to the Crisp integration settings page\n- Populate the dropdown with the user's existing Kanban boards fetched from the database\n- Persist the selected board ID to the user/tenant settings\n- Display a clear label and helper text explaining how this board will be used for auto-assigned action items\n\n---\n\nAutomatic Action Item Extraction\n\n- Remove the dependency on the manual \"Extract Action Items\" button for new Crisp conversations\n- Trigger extraction automatically when a Crisp conversation is ingested or updated via webhook\n- Use AI to parse the conversation transcript and identify discrete action items, including:\n  - The action item description\n  - The assignee (if mentioned or inferable)\n  - A due date or urgency (if mentioned)\n  - The source conversation/meeting reference\n\n---\n\nAction Items Persistence\n\n- Create an action_items table (if one does not already exist) with at minimum the following fields:\n  - id, meeting_id / conversation_id, description, assignee, due_date, status, created_at, updated_at\n- On extraction, upsert action items to this table so re-processing does not create duplicates\n- Ensure action items are scoped correctly to the tenant/user for multi-tenant safety\n- Verify the existing \"Extract Action Items\" button also writes results to this table (fix the current bug where items are not persisted)\n\n---\n\nMeeting Details Page — Action Items Tab\n\n- On page load, fetch and display persisted action items from the database rather than requiring manual extraction\n- Remove or repurpose the \"Extract Action Items\" button — consider changing it to a \"Re-extract\" or \"Refresh\" secondary action so users can still trigger manual re-processing if needed\n- Show a loading/empty state if no action items have been extracted yet\n- Display each action item with its description, assignee, status, and due date if available\n\n---\n\nKanban Auto-Assignment\n\n- After extraction, identify action items where the assignee matches the currently authenticated user\n- Automatically create a card for each matched action item on the user's configured default Kanban board (set in the Crisp integration settings)\n- If no default board has been configured, surface a prompt or notification guiding the user to configure one\n- Prevent duplicate cards if the action item has already been added to the board (idempotency check)\n- Link the Kanban card back to the source meeting/conversation for traceability\n\n---\n\nEdge Cases to Consider\n\n- Crisp conversation contains no identifiable action items — handle gracefully with an appropriate empty state\n- Assignee mentioned in conversation does not match any known user — store the item but do not auto-assign to Kanban\n- Default Kanban board is deleted after being set — detect and prompt the user to reconfigure\n- Webhook fires multiple times for the same conversation — ensure extraction and card creation are idempotent\n- Multi-tenant isolation — action items and Kanban cards must never leak across tenants",
  "title": "Automate Action Item Extraction and Kanban Integration",
